Constructor Detail

Lap

Lap(java.lang.String name,
    long t0,
    long period,
    boolean delayed,
    int historyDepth,
    LapAction action,
    PerformanceMonitor monitor)
Defaul constructor. Only PerformanceMonitor is in charge of creating and managing Lap objects, and so is is a Factory for this class.

Parameters:
name - the Lap Name
t0 - lap initial time
period - lap period
delayed - if true, the first period duration will be (period - currentTimeMillis%period).
historyDepth - lap history depth
action - the lap lapAction
monitor - the lap monitor

setLogger

public void setLogger(org.apache.log4j.Logger logger,
                      org.apache.log4j.Level level,
                      java.lang.String loggerPrefix)
This method sets a logger (log4j) for the Lap. If a logger is setted the Lap will write to the logger any lap with INFO priority.

Parameters:
logger - the logger to set for this lap.
level - the log level for this lap.
loggerPrefix - the logger prefix string.

lap

final void lap(long timeMillis)
Closes a "lap". During this operation the Lap updates his history and logger (if any), and checks all his alarms.

Parameters:
timeMillis - lap closure time.

addEventsAlarm

public final void addEventsAlarm(Alarm alarm)
Adds an event alarm to the lap. Events alarms are raised based on the number of processed events in the lap period.

Parameters:
alarm - the event alarm

addRateAlarm

public final void addRateAlarm(Alarm alarm)
Adds a rate alarm to the lap. Rate alarms are raised based on the current processing rate in the lap period.

Parameters:
alarm - the rate alarm

addAverageLatencyAlarm
